<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,685,962]" pageId="8" pageNumber="249">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,757,782]" pageId="8" pageNumber="249">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Viraktamath" box="[668,890,757,782]" pageId="8" pageNumber="249" refString="Viraktamath, C. A. (2011) Revision of the Oriental and Australian Agalliini (Hemiptera: Cicadellidae: Megophthalminae). Zootaxa, 2844, 1 - 118." type="journal article" year="2011">
Viraktamath (
<number box="[822,882,758,782]" pageId="8" pageNumber="249" value="2011.0">2011</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, and its male genitalia exhibit minor variation in the ventral margin of the aedeagal shaft which is either straight as in the 
<typeStatus box="[967,1065,793,818]" pageId="8" pageNumber="249">holotype</typeStatus>
(Fig. 
<number box="[1133,1178,794,818]" pageId="8" pageNumber="249" value="348.0">348</number>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Viraktamath" box="[1189,1398,793,818]" pageId="8" pageNumber="249" refString="Viraktamath, C. A. (2011) Revision of the Oriental and Australian Agalliini (Hemiptera: Cicadellidae: Megophthalminae). Zootaxa, 2844, 1 - 118." type="journal article" year="2011">
Viraktamath, 
<number box="[1341,1398,794,818]" pageId="8" pageNumber="249" value="2011.0">2011</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) or sinuate as in the 
<typeStatus box="[337,434,830,854]" pageId="8" pageNumber="249">paratype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation box="[449,580,829,854]" captionStart="FIGURES 37 – 44" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[201,1394,228,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[155,1432,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 37 – 44. Habitus, face and genitalia male Igerna priyankae Viraktamath 37, 38. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 39. Face; 40. Subgenital plate; 41. Pygofer, lateral view; 42. Anal collar process; 43. Aedeagus with style; 44. Aedeagus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242866/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="249">
Figs 
<number box="[505,580,830,854]" pageId="8" pageNumber="249" value="43.5" valueMax="44.0" valueMin="43.0">43–44</number>
</figureCitation>
). These seem to be intraspecific variation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,685,962]" pageId="8" pageNumber="249">
In the key to the species of 
<taxonomicName box="[505,580,866,889]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Igerna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="249" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[505,580,866,889]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="249">Igerna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Oriental region by 
<bibRefCitation author="Viraktamath" box="[869,1090,865,890]" pageId="8" pageNumber="249" refString="Viraktamath, C. A. (2011) Revision of the Oriental and Australian Agalliini (Hemiptera: Cicadellidae: Megophthalminae). Zootaxa, 2844, 1 - 118." type="journal article" year="2011">
Viraktamath (
<number box="[1022,1082,866,890]" pageId="8" pageNumber="249" value="2011.0">2011</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, couplet 
<number box="[1191,1219,866,890]" pageId="8" pageNumber="249" value="12.0">12</number>
can be modified as follows to include the two new species currently described herein along with the other two species from 
<collectingCountry box="[1314,1381,901,926]" name="China" pageId="8" pageNumber="249">China</collectingCountry>
viz., 
<taxonomicName authority="Viraktamath" authorityName="Viraktamath" authorityYear="2012" box="[151,612,937,962]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Igerna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="249" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="channa">
<emphasis box="[151,315,937,961]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="249">Igerna channa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[322,612,937,962]" pageId="8" pageNumber="249" refString="Viraktamath, C. A., Dai, W. &amp; Zhang, Y. (2012) Taxonomic revision of the leafhopper tribe Agalliini (Hemiptera: Cicadellidae: Megophthalminae) from China, with description of new taxa. Zootaxa, 3430, 1 - 49." type="journal article">
Viraktamath, 
<emphasis box="[474,522,937,961]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="249">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[545,604,938,962]" pageId="8" pageNumber="249" value="2012.0">2012</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Li" authorityName="Li" authorityYear="2012" box="[666,1039,937,962]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Igerna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="249" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenuicula">
<emphasis box="[666,852,937,961]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="249">Igerna tenuicula</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[859,1039,937,962]" pageId="8" pageNumber="249" refString="Li, H., Dai, R. H. &amp; Li, Z. Z. (2012) First record of the leafhopper Genus Igerna (Hemiptera: Cicadellidae: Megophthalminae) in China with a description of a new species. Florida Entomologist, 95 (4), 979 - 982. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1653 / 024.095.0424" type="journal article">
Li, 
<emphasis box="[898,947,937,961]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="249">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[969,1031,938,962]" pageId="8" pageNumber="249" value="2012.0">2012</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
